2 Development

2.1 Climate change in the USA

In this section, we are uploading all the data that will be used in the following steps.

#sink(tempfile())

# Importing us_states data
sf.usstates <- us_states
# Load as a raster
SPEI_US_data <- rast(file.path(path_data, 'spei01.nc'))
# Matching coordinate system
# Check and match the CRS (Coordinate Reference System)
us_states <- st_transform(us_states, crs(SPEI_US_data))

#sink()

We are calculating the average SPEI index across regions over the past 50 years.

# Aggregating data by region
sink(tempfile())
# Dissolve state polygons into regional polygons
us_regions <- us_states %>%
  group_by(REGION) %>%
  summarise(geometry = st_union(geometry), .groups = "drop")

# Getting raster time information
time_info <- time(SPEI_US_data)

# Find the index of the first occurrence of "1966"
start_index <- which(grepl("^1966", time_info))[1]

# Select last 50 years (~600 months)
end_index <- start_index + 599  

# Select raster layers from 1966 to 2015
SPEI_recent <- SPEI_US_data[[start_index:end_index]]

spei_list <- list()

for (i in 1:50) {
  # Compute mean over 12 months first
  yearly_spei_mean <- app(SPEI_recent[[((i-1) * 12 + 1):(i * 12)]], mean)
  
  # Extract mean SPEI per region for the year
  spei_mean <- exact_extract(yearly_spei_mean, us_regions, fun = "mean") 
  
  spei_list[[i]] <- spei_mean
}
sink()

# Convert to matrix
spei_matrix <- do.call(cbind, spei_list)

# Check dimensions
# dim(spei_matrix)  # dim return (4, 50)

# Add column names for each year
colnames(spei_matrix) <- paste0(1966:2015)

# Attach SPEI data to `us_regions`
us_regions_spei <- cbind(us_regions, spei_matrix)
# Remove the "X" prefix from numeric column names
colnames(us_regions_spei) <- gsub("^X", "", colnames(us_regions_spei))


# Convert sf object to a normal data frame
df_normal <- us_regions_spei %>% st_drop_geometry()

# Ensure column names are properly formatted as characters
colnames(df_normal) <- as.character(colnames(df_normal))

print(colnames(df_normal))
##  [1] "REGION" "1966"   "1967"   "1968"   "1969"   "1970"   "1971"   "1972"  
##  [9] "1973"   "1974"   "1975"   "1976"   "1977"   "1978"   "1979"   "1980"  
## [17] "1981"   "1982"   "1983"   "1984"   "1985"   "1986"   "1987"   "1988"  
## [25] "1989"   "1990"   "1991"   "1992"   "1993"   "1994"   "1995"   "1996"  
## [33] "1997"   "1998"   "1999"   "2000"   "2001"   "2002"   "2003"   "2004"  
## [41] "2005"   "2006"   "2007"   "2008"   "2009"   "2010"   "2011"   "2012"  
## [49] "2013"   "2014"   "2015"
# Apply pivot_longer() after removing geometry
df_long <- df_normal %>%
  pivot_longer(
    cols = -REGION,    # Exclude the "REGION" column
    names_to = "Year",  # Column names become "Year"
    values_to = "Value", # Values go into "Value"
    values_drop_na = TRUE
  ) %>%
  mutate(Year = as.integer(Year))  # Convert Year column to numeric if needed

Finally, we can observe the figure showing the evolution of the SPEI index for each region.

ggplot(df_long, aes(x = Year, y = Value, color = REGION)) +
  geom_line(size = 1) +  # Line plot for each region
  geom_smooth(method = "loess", color = "blue", size = 1.5, se = TRUE) +  # Smoothed trend line
  theme_minimal() +
  labs(title = "SPEI Trends by Region (1966-2015)",
       x = "Year",
       y = "SPEI",
       color = "REGION") +
  theme(legend.position = "right")

  geom_sf(data = spain_cities_graph, 
          aes(color = NAME, shape = NAME), size = 4) +  # Cities with different markers
  scale_shape_manual(values = city_shapes) +  # Assigning shapes
  scale_color_manual(values = city_colors) +  # Assigning colors
  labs(title = "Road Network in Spain", color = "City", shape = "City") +  # Legend
  theme_minimal()

Rasterizing:

ne1_raster_line <- ne1_raster[[1]]

spain_border <- st_transform(spain_border, crs(ne1_raster_line))

ne1_raster_cropped <- crop(ne1_raster_line, ext(spain_border))

# Masking to get rid of the surroundings
ne1_raster_masked <- mask(ne1_raster_cropped, vect(spain_border))

# Convert city coordinates to spatial points
city_points <- st_as_sf(spain_cities, coords = c("longitude", "latitude"), crs = st_crs(friction_surface))

city_points_vect <- vect(city_points)


# Extract values from the raster at city locations
city_raster_values <- extract(ne1_raster_masked, city_points_vect)

# Convert to a data frame for easier viewing
city_raster_df <- data.frame(
  City = spain_cities$NAMEASCII,
  Raster_Value = city_raster_values
)

# Print extracted raster values for each city
print(city_raster_df)

  rownames_to_column(var = "origin") %>%
